{{Infobox website | name = Anime News Network | logo = Anime News Network logo.png | logo_size = 250px | screenshot = | caption = Anime News Network logo | url = {{URL|https://www.animenewsnetwork.com}} | commercial = Yes | type = [[Anime]] | language = [[English language|English]] | country = [[Canada]]<ref name="Location">{{cite web|title=Where is ANN based?|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/faq#where_is_ann_based|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=9 February 2017}}</ref> | registration = Required for use of forums or contributing information | author = Justin Sevakis and others<ref name="who operates">{{cite web|title=Who operates ANN?|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/faq#who_operates_ann|work=FAQ|publisher= Anime News Network|accessdate=2008-01-22| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080118095303/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/faq| archivedate= 18 January 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Staff List|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/staff.php|publisher=Anime News Network|year=2007|accessdate=2016-02-10| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080120062040/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/staff.php| archivedate= 20 January 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref> | launch date = {{start date and age|1998|8|21}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://whois.domaintools.com/animenewsnetwork.com|title=AnimeNewsNetwork.com WHOIS, DNS, & Domain Info - DomainTools|work=[[WHOIS]]|date= |accessdate=2016-10-13}}</ref> | current status = Active | revenue = | alexa = {{increase}} [http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/animenewsnetwork.com 4,225]{{small|{{nowrap|(Global, {{as of|2018|08|04|alt=August 2018}})}}}} <!--Updated monthly by OKBot. Updated manually since it hasn't been updated in YEARS...--> }}
'''Anime News Network''' ('''ANN''') is an [[anime industry]] [[news]] [[website]] that reports on the status of [[anime]], [[manga]], [[video games]], [[J-pop|Japanese popular music]] and other related cultures within [[North America]], [[Australia]], [[South East Asia]] and [[Japan]]. Additionally, it sometimes features similar happenings throughout the world.<ref name="what is ann">{{cite web|title=What is ANN?|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/faq#what_is_ann|work=FAQ|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=2008-02-18| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080218134105/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/faq| archivedate= 18 February 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref> The website offers reviews and other editorial content, [[Internet forum|forums]] where readers can discuss current issues and events, and an encyclopedia that contains a large number of anime and manga with information on Japanese and English staff, [[theme songs]], [[plot (narrative)|plot]] summaries, and user ratings.<ref name="scifiweekly">{{cite web | last=Dellamonica | first=A.M. | title=Site of the Week - Anime News Network | work=[[Sci Fi Weekly]] | publisher=SciFi.com | date=2004-09-07 | url=http://www.scifi.com/sfw/sites/sfw11410.html | accessdate=2007-12-16 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080116091348/http://www.scifi.com/sfw/sites/sfw11410.html |archivedate = 2008-01-16}}</ref>
Founded in July 1998 by Justin Sevakis, the website claims to be the leading English-language source for news and information about anime and manga on the Internet.<ref name="what is ann"/> The site operated, until 2008, the magazine ''[[Protoculture Addicts]]''.<ref name="join forces">{{cite press release | title = Anime News Network and Protoculture Addicts Join Forces | publisher = [[Protoculture Addicts]] | date = 2004-09-18 | url = http://www.protoculture.ca/PA/PR040918.htm | accessdate = 2008-01-22}}</ref> The website has separate versions of its news content aimed towards audiences in four separate regions: the [[United States]] and [[Canada]], [[Australia]]<ref name="australia">{{cite web|title=Anime News Network Australia|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-01-25/anime-network-australia|publisher=Anime News Network|date=2007-01-25|accessdate=2008-01-22| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080130115047/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-01-25/anime-network-australia| archivedate= 30 January 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref> and [[New Zealand]], the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Ireland]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Re-announcing ANN UK & Australia|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/site-news/2011-03-25/welcome-to-ann-uk/au|publisher=Anime News Network|date=2011-03-25|accessdate=2011-08-08}}</ref> and [[Southeast Asia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Welcome to Anime News Network Southeast Asia!|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/site-news/2015-10-30/welcome-to-anime-news-network-southeast-asia/.94722|publisher=Anime News Network|date=2015-10-29|accessdate=2016-10-13}}</ref>
==History== The website was founded by Justin Sevakis in July 1998.<ref name="what is ann"/> In May 2000, current CEO Christopher Macdonald joined the website editorial staff, replacing former editor-in-chief Isaac Alexander. In July 2002, Anime News Network launched its Encyclopedia, a collaborative database of anime and manga titles also including information about the staff, cast, and companies involved in the production or localization of those titles. In January 2007, ANN launched a separate version for [[Australia]]n audiences.<ref name="australia"/> On July 4, 2008, ANN launched its video platform with a library of anime trailers as well as its own news show ANNtv.
In the fall of 2004, the editorial staff at ANN became formally involved with the anime magazine ''[[Protoculture Addicts]]''; the magazine began publishing under ANN's editorial control in January 2005.<ref name="join forces"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Crocker|first=Janet|title=Addicts Nip/Tuck|url=http://www.animefringe.com/magazine/2004/10/feature/05.php|work=Anime Fringe|date=October 2004|accessdate=2008-02-18}}</ref> On September 7, 2004, the [[Syfy|Sci Fi Channel]] online newsletter ''[[Sci Fi Weekly]]'' named the site the Web Site of the Week.<ref
==Features== Anime News Network stories related to anime and manga that are researched by the ANN staff. Other contributors, under staff discretion, also contribute news articles.<ref name="can i submit">{{cite web|title=Can I submit an article?|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/faq#submit_articles|work=FAQ|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=2008-02-18| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080218134105/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/faq| archivedate= 18 February 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref>
The website maintains a listing of anime and manga titles, as well as people and companies involved in the production of those titles, which it dubs an "encyclopedia".<ref name="scifiweekly"/> The site has hosted several regular columns, including a question-and-answer column "Hey Answerman", a review column entitled "Shelf Life", a column on old and forgotten media called "Buried Treasure" written by Sevakis,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/buried-treasure |title=Buried Treasure |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2012-11-07 |accessdate=2012-11-11}}</ref> and a listing of claimed differences between edited and original versions of anime series titled "The Edit List".<ref>{{cite web|title=Columns|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/views|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=2008-02-18| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080218082232/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/views| archivedate= 18 February 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref> Staff members of ANN also publish their own blogs hosted on the site.<ref>{{cite web|title=ANN Staff and Industry Blogs|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/blogs/|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=2008-02-21| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080226095100/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/blogs/| archivedate= 26 February 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref>
ANN also hosts [[internet forum|forums]],<ref name="scifiweekly"/> and includes threads to accompany each news item for purposes of discussion. Anime News Network hosts an [[Internet Relay Chat|IRC]] channel on the WorldIRC network, #animenewsnetwork.
On August 7, 2017, a hacker took control of Anime News Network's domain (animenewsnetwork.com), and compromised some of the site's Twitter accounts, including the personal accounts of ANN's CEO Christopher Macdonald and Executive Editor Zac Bertschy. The site was temporarily live at animenewsnetwork.cc until the staff regained control of the original domain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/site-news/2017-08-08/update-what-going-on-with-anime-news-network/.119882 |title=What's Going On with Anime News Network? |website=Anime News Network |date=August 8, 2017 |accessdate=August 14, 2017}}</ref> In an article a few days after the loss of the domain, Macdonald published the full story on how the domain was stolen.<ref>{{cite web |first=Christopher |last=Macdonald |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/site-news/2017-08-11/how-ann-was-hacked/.120038 |title=How ANN Was Hacked |date=August 11, 2017 |accessdate=August 14, 2017}}</ref>
