{{Infobox company | name = '''CIVIC''' | type = | logo = | foundation = 1985 | defunct = 2018 | location = [[Alexandria, New South Wales]], [[Australia]] | area_served = [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]] | key_people = | num_employees = | parent = '''Civic Retailing Pty Ltd''' | industry = [[Video rental]] | homepage = [http://www.civicvideo.com.au Civic Video] }}
[[File:Civic cards.jpg|thumb|right|Civic Video reward cards]] '''CIVIC''' (formerly known as Civic Video) was a VHS, DVD, Blu-ray, Ultra HD Blu-ray, and video game rental store chain which operates [[franchising|franchise]] and corporate-owned video stores in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]].
<!-- == History == -->
==Australia== [[File:Civic Video Wagga.jpg|thumb|Civic Video store in [[Wagga Wagga, New South Wales]].]] Civic Video was formed in Australia in 1985. The head office is located in [[Alexandria, Sydney]], with state operations offices in [[Canberra]], [[Brisbane]] and [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]]. As of April 2018, 13 stores remained in Australia.<ref>[https://www.busseltonmail.com.au/story/5339909/civic-videos-closing-credits/ Civic Video's closing credits | Busselton-Dunsborough Mail]</ref> Since then, at least one more store has closed.<ref>[https://thewest.com.au/news/augusta-margaret-river-times/video-store-close-down-marks-end-of-an-era-ng-b88886207z Video store close-down marks end of an era | The West Australian]</ref>
== New Zealand == [[File:Civic Video Ponsonby.JPG|thumb|Civic Video, Ponsonby Road, [[New Zealand]]]] CIVIC New Zealand (formerly Civic Video) was launched on 1 December 1998 with 28 stores. Their homepage lists 20 outlets remaining in New Zealand.<ref>[https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=11988904 Final credits for Te Awamutu's last DVD store - NZ Herald]</ref> The New Zealand head office is located in Auckland. CIVIC are New Zealand's most "liked" DVD and Blu-ray stores with over 22,000 followers on Facebook.
==Corporation== Civic Video is a [[trade name]] used by '''Civic Retailing Pty Ltd''', based in Alexandria, New South Wales.<ref>{{cite web |title=Civic Video Privacy Policy |publisher=Civic Video Entertainment, Inc. |url=http://www.civicvideo.com.au/browse.asp?ContainerID=privacy_policy |accessdate=2008-03-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080719131252/http://www.civicvideo.com.au/browse.asp?ContainerID=privacy_policy |archivedate=19 July 2008 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The principal shareholders of Civic Video also own VOD Pty Ltd.<ref>{{cite press release |title=Concurrent Computer and VOD Pty Ltd Take Video-On-Demand 'Down Under' with Australia's First Commercial Deployment |date=27 June 2001 |publisher=[[Concurrent Computer Corporation]] |url=http://ccur.com/corp_news_pressrelease.asp?pressreleaseid=154 |accessdate=2008-03-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041215023443/http://www.ccur.com/corp_news_pressrelease.asp?pressreleaseid=154 |archivedate=15 December 2004 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
